'''Kamay Lau''' is a model and actress from [[Wikipedia:London|London]], [[Wikipedia:United Kingdom|U.K.]] In [[1999]], she played [[Sei Taria]], an [[Administrator|administrative]] [[aide]] to [[Supreme Chancellor|Chancellor]] [[Finis Valorum|Valorum]], in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']].<ref name="Kamay" />

Prior to entering the acting industry, Lau was a [[Wikipedia:Fashion design|fashion designer]] and stylist. She obtained a degree in Fashion Design from [[Wikipedia:Kwantlen Polytechnic University|Kwantlen Polytechnic University]] in [[Wikipedia:Vancouver|Vancouver]], [[Wikipedia:British Columbia|British Columbia]] in [[1982]], and a further degree in Fashion Technology from the American Fashion Institute in [[Wikipedia:Paris|Paris]], [[Wikipedia:France|France]] in [[1985]]. In [[1997]], Lau took an Improvisation Course at London's Holborn Arts Center.<ref name="Kamay" />

Lau has acting and modeling experience in fashion, film, and television.<ref name="Kamay" /> In addition to her role in ''The Phantom Menace'', she has appeared in [[Wikipedia:The Fifth Element|''The Fifth Element'']] (1997), [[Wikipedia:Lost In Space (film)|''Lost In Space'']] ([[1998]]),<ref name="imdb">{{IMDb|name/nm2151895}}</ref> [[Wikipedia:Guy Ritchie|Guy Ritchie's]] [[Wikipedia:Revolver (2005 film)|''Revolver'']] ([[2005]]) and in the [[Wikipedia:BBC|BBC]] television drama [[Wikipedia:A for Andromeda (2006)|''A for Andromeda'']] ([[2006]]). Lau later went on to feature in a four-week long fashion spread for mature models in [[Wikipedia:The Guardian|''The Guardian'']] newspaper in [[2006]] and to appear on the front cover of ''Prudential'' magazine. In [[2009]], she was in the U.K.'s National Express Campaign and appeared in images at bus stops throughout the country.<ref name="Kamay" />

